    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers Scarlet/aswritten **style and information-architecture observations** — how the documents physically encode argument. The dominant claim across children is that *structure carries the thesis*: markdown tables are treated as the canonical statement, not the prose ([three-tool table as definition](narr:StyleObs_TableDrivenArchitecture), [Tool|Question|Input|Output matrix](narr:StyleObs_FiveToolTable), [tiered-inference table](narr:StyleObs_SelfHosted_TableStructure), [acquirer/range tables](narr:StyleObs_TableHeavyStructure)). Lists do the same work — [Priority-labeled planning memos](narr:StyleObs_DirectListFormat), [What-changed/didn't bullets](narr:StyleObs_BulletedDecisionFormat_Distillation), [parallel design-implication lists](narr:StyleObs_TemporalityValidation_BulletedDesignImplications). Bold inline anchors recur as scannable navigation within flowing prose ([the-frame anchors](narr:StyleObs_BoldSectionHeaders), [≈ mapping headers](narr:StyleObs_AgentSim_BoldHeaders)), and [numbered claim-IRI taxonomies](narr:StyleObs_ARB_TaxonomicStructure) supply cross-referencing convention. Dates span Mar 2025–May 2026; the pattern is consistent across the idiolect, not evolving toward a verdict.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_9> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_ARB_TaxonomicStructure> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_ActionItemList> ;
